01:46:01,154 --> 01:46:03,034
at the beginning and end of the trajectory.

2830
01:46:04,114 --> 01:46:04,714
So,

2831
01:46:04,714 --> 01:46:06,414
if this contributes something

2832
01:46:07,114 --> 01:46:08,794
which doesn't depend on the trajectory,

2833
01:46:09,114 --> 01:46:11,514
it will not have any influence whatever

2834
01:46:12,874 --> 01:46:15,474
on what trajectory the particle takes.

2835
01:46:15,814 --> 01:46:17,154
And in that sense,

2836
01:46:17,254 --> 01:46:20,274
this is not an interesting contribution to the action.

2837
01:46:20,514 --> 01:46:22,934
It has no implication for the motion of the particle.

2838
01:46:23,214 --> 01:46:25,974
The important part of the action doesn't change

2839
01:46:25,974 --> 01:46:28,094
the part which really influences

2840
01:46:28,114 --> 01:46:29,694
the particle does not change

2841
01:46:29,694 --> 01:46:31,174
when you make a gauge transformation.

2842
01:46:31,674 --> 01:46:32,294
So,

2843
01:46:32,294 --> 01:46:34,014
we see from this particle perspective

2844
01:46:34,873 --> 01:46:37,654
that gauge transformations are also important

2845
01:46:37,654 --> 01:46:41,214
in variances of the action of a charged particle

2846
01:46:41,214 --> 01:46:43,494
with the electromagnetic field.

2847
01:46:44,614 --> 01:46:45,254
So,

2848
01:46:45,254 --> 01:46:46,254
this time,

2849
01:46:46,254 --> 01:46:48,834
we're not talking about a field

2850
01:46:48,834 --> 01:46:49,954
carrying the charge.

2851
01:46:50,154 --> 01:46:51,714
We're just talking about a point charge

2852
01:46:51,714 --> 01:46:52,834
moving through space.

2853
01:46:55,834 --> 01:46:56,414
So,

2854
01:46:56,414 --> 01:46:58,014
we see from two different perspectives

2855
01:46:58,734 --> 01:47:02,294
that gauge symmetry is a fundamental symmetry

2856
01:47:02,294 --> 01:47:03,934
of the interaction of charges

2857
01:47:03,934 --> 01:47:06,174
with the electromagnetic field.

2858
01:47:07,894 --> 01:47:10,154
I will be gone next week.

2859
01:47:10,254 --> 01:47:11,894
I have to give a lecture someplace.

2860
01:47:12,254 --> 01:47:13,434
A couple of places.

2861
01:47:14,774 --> 01:47:16,894
And I'll be back the week after.

2862
01:47:17,614 --> 01:47:19,794
How many lessons have we had so far?

2863
01:47:20,994 --> 01:47:21,574
Seven.

2864
01:47:22,534 --> 01:47:23,014
Eight.

2865
01:47:23,414 --> 01:47:24,794
Seems to me it must be eight.

2866
01:47:25,134 --> 01:47:25,614
Yeah.

2867
01:47:25,934 --> 01:47:26,414
So,

2868
01:47:26,414 --> 01:47:26,954
we have two more.

2869
01:47:29,254 --> 01:47:31,994
And I think we're getting somewhere.

2870
01:47:32,594 --> 01:47:33,074
We've,

2871
01:47:33,074 --> 01:47:33,654
you know,

2872
01:47:33,654 --> 01:47:34,634
but I want to,

2873
01:47:34,654 --> 01:47:35,774
what I do want to go through now

2874
01:47:35,774 --> 01:47:38,174
is the electromagnetic field,

2875
01:47:38,694 --> 01:47:41,434
the equations of motion for the electromagnetic field,

2876
01:47:41,654 --> 01:47:45,794
why F mu nu is connected to E and B,

2877
01:47:47,034 --> 01:47:50,034
and to see that the electromagnetic field

2878
01:47:50,034 --> 01:47:51,474
actually has the effect

2879
01:47:51,574 --> 01:47:53,414
on a charged particle that you would expect,

2880
01:47:54,274 --> 01:47:57,134
namely that it exerts forces

2881
01:47:57,134 --> 01:47:59,154
of the electrical and magnetic kind.

2882
01:48:00,214 --> 01:48:01,904
Then we could maybe spend a

2883
01:48:01,904 --> 01:48:03,594
little bit of time with this

2884
01:48:03,594 --> 01:48:06,214
and see that the flow of charge

2885
01:48:06,214 --> 01:48:09,154
in this picture here also behaves

2886
01:48:09,154 --> 01:48:12,574
as you would expect for charges flowing through space

2887
01:48:12,574 --> 01:48:15,014
if the charges were described by this field.

2888
